<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1893-02-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1893-02-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="201" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d201">
                            <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Stevens</persName> to
                                    Mr. <persName type="to">Foster</persName>.</hi></head>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Honolulu</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1893-02-08"><hi rend="italic">February 8, 1893</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                            <p>The affairs of state continue to be hopeful. Hoisting flag in
                                protection of this Government was expected. Subjects who were
                                doubtful, now for annexation. The natives showed unexpected regard
                                of the United States flag. Prudent conduct of Capt. Wiltse, the
                                officers and crew of the <hi rend="italic">Boston</hi>, credit to
                                the Navy. Can not send by mail.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stevens.</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>